==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chard
<hw>Chard</hw> <pr>(ch⟦aum⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>carde</ets> esculent thistle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The tender
leaves or leafstalks of the artichoke, white beet, etc., blanched for
table use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A variety of the white beet, which produces large,
succulent leaves and leafstalks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chardonnay</ent>⟦br⟧
